Invoke a contract function

Generates an "implicit CLI" for the specified contract on-the-fly using the contract's schema, which gets embedded into every Soroban contract. The "slop" in this command, everything after the `--`, gets passed to this implicit CLI. Get in-depth help for a given contract:

stellar contract invoke ... -- --help

Usage: stellar.exe contract invoke [OPTIONS] --id <CONTRACT_ID> --source-account <SOURCE_ACCOUNT> [-- <CONTRACT_FN_AND_ARGS>...]

Arguments:
  [CONTRACT_FN_AND_ARGS]...
          Function name as subcommand, then arguments for that function as `--arg-name value`

Options:
      --id <CONTRACT_ID>
          Contract ID to invoke
          
          [env: STELLAR_CONTRACT_ID=]

      --is-view
          ⚠️ Deprecated, use `--send=no`. View the result simulating and do not sign and submit transaction
          
          [env: STELLAR_INVOKE_VIEW=]

  -s, --source-account <SOURCE_ACCOUNT>
          Account that where transaction originates from. Alias `source`. Can be an identity (--source alice), a public key (--source GDKW...), a muxed account (--source MDA…), a secret key (--source SC36…), or a seed phrase (--source "kite urban…"). If `--build-only` or `--sim-only` flags were NOT provided, this key will also be used to sign the final transaction. In that case, trying to sign with public key will fail
          
          [env: STELLAR_ACCOUNT=]
          [aliases: --source]

      --sign-with-key <SIGN_WITH_KEY>
          Sign with a local key or key saved in OS secure storage. Can be an identity (--sign-with-key alice), a secret key (--sign-with-key SC36…), or a seed phrase (--sign-with-key "kite urban…"). If using seed phrase, `--hd-path` defaults to the `0` path
          
          [env: STELLAR_SIGN_WITH_KEY=]

      --hd-path <HD_PATH>
          If using a seed phrase to sign, sets which hierarchical deterministic path to use, e.g. `m/44'/148'/{hd_path}`. Example: `--hd-path 1`. Default: `0`

      --sign-with-lab
          Sign with https://lab.stellar.org
          
          [env: STELLAR_SIGN_WITH_LAB=]

      --sign-with-ledger
          Sign with a ledger wallet
          
          [env: STELLAR_SIGN_WITH_LEDGER=]

      --send <SEND>
          Whether or not to send a transaction

          Possible values:
          - default: Send transaction if simulation indicates there are ledger writes, published events, or auth required, otherwise return simulation result
          - no:      Do not send transaction, return simulation result
          - yes:     Always send transaction
          
          [env: STELLAR_SEND=]
          [default: default]

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')

Options (RPC):
      --rpc-url <RPC_URL>
          RPC server endpoint
          
          [env: STELLAR_RPC_URL=]

      --rpc-header <RPC_HEADERS>
          RPC Header(s) to include in requests to the RPC provider, example: "X-API-Key: abc123". Multiple headers can be added by passing the option multiple times
          
          [env: STELLAR_RPC_HEADERS=]

      --network-passphrase <NETWORK_PASSPHRASE>
          Network passphrase to sign the transaction sent to the rpc server
          
          [env: STELLAR_NETWORK_PASSPHRASE=]

  -n, --network <NETWORK>
          Name of network to use from config
          
          [env: STELLAR_NETWORK=]

      --fee <FEE>
          fee amount for transaction, in stroops. 1 stroop = 0.0000001 xlm
          
          [env: STELLAR_FEE=]
          [default: 100]

      --cost
          Output the cost execution to stderr

      --instructions <INSTRUCTIONS>
          Number of instructions to simulate

      --instruction-leeway <INSTRUCTION_LEEWAY>
          Allow this many extra instructions when budgeting resources during transaction simulation

      --build-only
          Build the transaction and only write the base64 xdr to stdout

Options (Global):
  -f, --filter-logs <FILTER_LOGS>
          Filter logs output. To turn on `stellar_cli::log::footprint=debug` or off `=off`. Can also use env var `RUST_LOG`

  -q, --quiet
          Do not write logs to stderr including `INFO`

  -v, --verbose
          Log DEBUG events

      --very-verbose
          Log DEBUG and TRACE events
          
          [aliases: --vv]

      --global
          ⚠️ Deprecated: global config is always on

      --no-cache
          Do not cache your simulations and transactions
          
          [env: STELLAR_NO_CACHE=]

      --config-dir <CONFIG_DIR>
          Location of config directory. By default, it uses `$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/stellar` if set, falling back to `~/.config/stellar` otherwise. Contains configuration files, aliases, and other persistent settings
